headline: CVS Health (CVS): Assessing Fair Value After Goodwill Impairment, Q3 Loss, and Revised Outlook
summary: CVS Health (CVS) recently posted a net loss for the third quarter, cut full-year earnings guidance, and reported a major goodwill impairment. These developments have investors rethinking the company’s near-term outlook and business momentum. See our latest analysis for CVS Health. While CVS Health’s hefty goodwill impairment and reduced earnings outlook have weighed on sentiment, the 20.6% share price return over the last 90 days suggests some investors see value after a tough stretch. headline: CVS Health to hold Investor Day on December 9, 2025

headline: TRIP, The World's Leading Calming Drinks Brand, Raises $40 Million
summary: TRIP announces a $40 million funding round – led by high-profile names such as Joe Jonas, Alessandra Ambrosio, Paul Wesley, Ashley Graham, and consumer fund Coefficient Capital. TRIP, the fastest growing drinks brand in the US this year (Spins) is on track to deliver $100 million in annual revenue this year and is predicted to reach $200 million in 2026.
